rum es-\n                                          to-layer interactions, and simple concatenation limits cross-\n                                          modal learning. We propose MOSAIC (Multi-token Oriented                   timator, but are typically evaluated as PA-only specialists\n                                          Speech Anti-spoofing via Integrated Cross-attention), an inter-           with no LA/DF figures reported. The broader open chal-\n                                          pretable multi-token cross-attention framework that splits a 152-         lenge is the move from controlled 2019 PA conditions to\n                                          dimensional biophonetic feature vector into six semantic-group            the diverse, in-the-wild ASVspoof 2021 PA benchmark with\n                                          query tokens (Praat, phase, LFCC mean/std, sub-band mean/std)             unseen microphones and rooms [1], where single-model ap-\n                                          and attends them over thirteen mean–std pooled WavLM-Large\n                                          transformer layers as keys/values. The resulting 6 × 13 attention         proaches that jointly handle LA and PA remain scarce. Recent\n                                          matrix visualizes cue-to-layer alignment; a z-score analysis of           SSL+handcrafted fusion — e.g., El Kheir et al.’s Two Views,\n                                          the per-token activations shows that biophonetic/phase tokens             One Truth [9], which pairs SSL features (as query) with\n                                          activate more on bona fide speech while spectral/channel tokens           spectral features MFCC/LFCC/CQCC (as key/value) for a\n                                          activate more on spoofed speech — yielding per-cue, per-layer             38 % relative EER reduction over SSL-only — retains a single\n                                     